inn1.comm: Nice probing start. Fullish, lands on the off stump line, goes on straight, Gayle pushes at it, gets a outside edge and runs to backward point
In the channel outside off stump, shapes in a touch, Chanderpaul leans across, covers his off stump and shoulders arms
lands on a length, on the middle stump line and moves in a touch and raps him on the thigh pad. There is some movement out there
Lands outside off stump, moves away, left alone
fuller, on the middle stump line, hint of inswing, Chanders flicks it to fine-leg
Hello? A low full-toss which swung away from Chanderpaul, pushed to third man
full and outside off stump, left alone
Bond is getting some swing out there. Starts from the middle and off , lands outside off stump and moves away sharply. Wide called and Bond is not impressed.
beaten. Fuller, swings away from the middle stump, Gayle stabs at it and the ball rushes past the outside edge. The seam is pointing towards slip.
Again another wide. Again huge swing. Swing and seam for Bond. If he gets it right, he could be a handful on this track
Banana swing. Starts from leg stump, moves in the air towards off stump, Gayle jabs at it, the ball lands and moves further away.
And again. This time Gayle lets it go through. He didn't shoulder his arms but played inside the line.
Similar line. In the temptation zone, left alone. Great start from Bond.
full in length, on the off stump line, straightens, pushed out to the on side
Fullish, outside off stump, Chanders leans forward, guides it to cover
teasing line outside off, Chanderpaul is not in a flirting mood, lets it go through.
fullish, on the middle, straightens after landing, Chanderpaul gets in line, works it to behind square-leg
takes this one away from Gayle who shoulders arms.
homing in on the off stump, Gayle leans forward and dead-bats it.
Full, on the middle stump line, swings away, Chanderpaul plays it late, pushes it to cover

What a beauty. Peach of a delivery. The swing started from the leg stump line, moved in the air, landed on the middle stump line and shaped away and Chanderpaul is beaten. Maybe... Bradman might have nicked that. Maybe....
on the middle and off, Chanderpaul moves into the line, steers to cover
on the leg stump line, lands on leg and middle, moves in towards off and middle, Chanderpaul does well to play it late, wait for the swing and then push it towards cover point for a quick single
Just short of driveable length, on the middle stump and it swings away. Gayle lets it go through to McCullum
whooshes through the air , on the legstump line, lands on the middle stump line and pushed out to the off side.
on the middle stump line, full in length, straightens, Chanderpaul turns it to the on side.
on the middle and off, moves away a touch, Chanderpaul is squared-up, opens the bat-face, steers to point
In the zone outside off stump, left alone
lands outside off stump, on a length, comes in a touch, Chanderpaul shuffles across, and lets that sail past him. Good probing stuff from the Kiwis
lands on the leg and middle, goes on straight, Chanderpaul gets right behind the line and defends
length-delivery on the middle and off stump line, Chanders presses forward to defend. Another tight over comes to an end. New Zealand are applying the squeeze.
Full, swings past the stumps and Gayle is cautious. Bat held close to the body, he moves across, covers the off stump and lets it fly past him. Bond is yet to bend the ball back in
Similar delivery, same shot. This is going to be a game of patience.
Gayle is the first one to make the move. He charges out, backs away in the process, and flat-bats a length-delivery over mid-off. Now what will Bond do? A yorker, slower one or a bouncer?
Nope, he sticks to that banana swing.  In the middle stump line, lands and then shapes away, Gayle plays inside the line
on the middle and off stump line, moves away a touch, Gayle shuffles across, pushes it out to point
full, on the leg stump line , swings in, lands on the middle stump line, shapes away, Gayle stays back, waits for the swing, plays with soft hands, towards cover. This is high quality stuff.
In the zone outside off stump, left alone
again Mason takes it away, another leave from Chanderpaul.
fuller, on the off stump line, Chanderpaul moves forward, the ball curves in a touch, and he pushes it back down the track
similar line, similar length but this one shapes away, Chanderpaul shapes to have a poke but pulls out at the last minute. Wise decision.
full in length, on the middle and leg stump line, straightens, Chanderpaul leans forward, dabs it to the on side
short in length, on the off stump line, Chanderpaul stands tall, pushes it down in front of him. Another tight over.
Fullish, on the middle and leg stump line, swings away a touch but Gayle flicks it through square-leg.
back of length, on the middle stump line, moves towards off, Gayle stands tall, punches it on the up towards mid-off where Franklin makes a neat diving stop
Change of pace. Gayle is through his shot early and that evades the bat and the 'keeper

Bond swings out his first victim. It moves in the air, on the middle and off stump line, lands on the off peg line, shapes away, Chanderpaul is sucked into a forward prod, bat well in front of the body, gets a nick and it is snaffled up by Styris at second slip.
back of length, outside off stump, comes in, Sarwan punches it through cover point

Fullish, on the middle stump line and Gayle drives, the bat-handle rotates, and the ball goes in the air to right of square-leg where Fulton stretches his right hand out and ends up palming it. Tough chance.
back of length, on the middle stump line, moves away, Gayle stays back, plays close to the body, pushes it out to the off side
short in length, on the middle stump line and Gayle pounces at it like a man starved off food. He rocks back and pulls it through midwicket. This is the first bad delivery of the day.
The second bad delivery follows quickly but Gayle misses the chance. Short and wide, Gayle tries to cut but makes contact with the bottom-half of the bat and it rolls towards point
Full in length, furious, on the off and middle stump line, Sarwan defends it on the front foot.
kicks up from short of length, Sarwan hops up and dead-bats it
another one which climbs from  short of length, pushed away. he is setting him up here. Watch out for the fullish and swinging one.
Sarwan gets off strike with a neat punch on the up to cover point. Again it was short in length.
short in length, slanting away from the off stump, Gayle leans back,  punches it to cover

Here comes the full one. On the leg stump line, moves in the air, Gayle is caught at his crease, pushes at it after taking out the bottom-hand out of the handle, the ball evades the waft and rams in to the thigh
Super stop from Hamish Marshall. Short in length, outside off stump and Sarwan slaps it on the up to right of cover - should have got four but Marshall dives to make the stop
outswinger outside off stump, Sarwan lets that one go through.
full in length, outside off stump, Sarwan eases into the line, drives to cover.
length-delivery on the off and middle stump line, Sarwan shuffles across and defends.
slips down the leg side, fourth poor delivery of the day, wide called.
short in length, outside off stump, straightens, Sarwan goes back and across, cuts but doesn't get much power behind that and the ball rolls towards point
full in length, outside off stump, Sarwan moves into the line, opens the bat-face, guides to point.
Fullish, on the off stump line, driven to mid-off. Gayle will look to take on Franklin
He is itching to get after him. Skips down the track, drives but straight to mid-off
short in length, outside off stump, Gayle moves in line and smashes it through point. Gayle will chance his arms against the gentle pace of Franklin and the lack of swing
on the middle stump line, from a length, defended to the on side
slightly short in length, coming in from outside off stump, Gayle leans back, tries to force it off the back foot but hits straight to cover
fuller, on the off and middle stump line, Gayle drives straight to Vettori at mid-on who fumbles but it doesn't prove costly
full in length, just outside off stump, Sarwan leans forward, drives to point
full again, driven to mid-off.
short in length, outside off stump, Sarwan cuts it to third man.
Length-delivery, outside off stump and Sarwan glides forward and drives on the up through extra cover. Fab shot.
short of length, well outside off stump, Sarwan goes for a cut, gets a top-edge that takes the ball over the slips, down to third man.
full in length, coming in from outside off stump, Gayle pushes it to the off side
similar delivery, Gayle takes out the front leg from the line and forces it off the back foot, to cover.
Franklin makes the mistake of pitching it up and Gayle goes down town. He leans forward, lofts it over mid-off.
Not-a-man-move. Length-delivery outside off stump and Gayle drilled it on the up through extra cover. Styris was standing at cover, couldn't do a thing, just had his hands on his knees.

Three in a row. Suddenly the floodgates are being prised open by the attacking Gayle. Similar delivery - coming in from outside off stump- and Gayle waited for it to arrive, opened the bat-face and thrashed it square, past point.
short in length, outside off stump and cut to point
length-delivery on the middle stump line, dabbed to the on side.
full in length, just outside off stump, Sarwan leans back, opens the bat-face, guides it to third man
lands on a length, on the middle and off stump line, pushed towards mid-off and they rush across for a quick single
Luckily the man moved this time. Full and outside off, Gayle biffed it straight, in the air, and Franklin ducked in time, else he would have been taken out.
again driven down the ground but there is a long on this time and they will get a single
clipped off the pads, behind square-leg, Sarwan pushes Gayle for the second run and they make it in time.

Fifty of the partnership up. In style. Sarwan glides forward to a length-delivery on the middle and off stump line and drives straight past the bowler. Easy on the eye. Perhaps.. the best shot of the day.
on the leg and middle, worked to long leg
leans forward, pushes a length-delivery to mid-off

Stunner from McCullum. Full in length, outside off stump and Sarwan drives but the bat comes outside the line as the ball moves in a touch, clips the inside-edge and it flies to the left of McCullum who dives full stretch to take a beauty. I would have said, another YouTube moment but ICC is watching. Shhhhh...
Good length outside off, defended confidently.
Slightly slower, good length outside off, patted to the on side
left alone outside off.
Good end to a tight over. Back of a length on off, Samuels gets behind the line and blocks. Wicket maiden from Oram.
Full outside off and Styris was lucky to see it crashed straight to cover. Fleming immediately puts a fielder in the off-side fence
pushed to the off side, better line, closer to the stumps
tries to glide to third man but too close to his body, misses
angled to shot third man, good stop there but can't prevent a run

Full delivery, only 66 mph, Samuels drives it down the ground and picks up a single. Almost as if he was driving a spinner there. Samuels can make batting look easy, sometimes too easy for his own comfort
Good finish, good length and outside off, blocked confidently
Good length ball outside off, Samuels plonks his foot forward and pushes confidently to cover
Beaten. Probing line outside off and moving away after pitching. Samuels pokes tentatively but can't get bat on ball. Just a few inches away from an edge
Glided to third man for a single. Slightly short of a length and Samuels angles his bat

Short of a length and outside off again, Gayle steers it to third man, runs the first one hard but decides against the second. His highest score of the tournament. He's been in poor form but will this be the day?
pushed off the front foot to cover. Samuels seems to be biding his time
And now he takes off. Smooth and effective. Slightly outside off, Samuels simply leans into it and finds the gap at cover. Went whistling between cover and mid-off, racing away to the fence.
Back of a length, forced through midwicket for a single
Defended confidently. Samuels seems in the mood today. Actually he always does, you never know what to expect
Turned away behind square, a mess up between two fielders (Mason and McMillan) and allows the batsmen a couple.
angled to third man for a single
worked away wide of mid-on, good sliding stop from Hamish Marshall but they complete a single easily
short of length, outside off stump, pushed to point
full in length, outside off stump, Samuels moves towards the line, drives to cover

Another one goes down. New Zealand are on fire. Lands short of length, just outside off stump, kicks up, Samuels is surprised by the extra bounce, tries to withdraw his bat from the line but it must have brushed his gloves enroute to McCullum.
Lands outside off stump, left alone
from round the stumps, another length-delivery through the channel outside off stump.
leans forward and defends a fullish delivery to the on side
lands outside off stump, turns in, Gayle backs away to cut to  sweeper cover
leans forward to defend
floated outside off, Lara leans forward, pushes it to cover
slow throug the air, outside off stump, again Gayle rocks back, cuts to cover
floated on the off and middle, not much to work with, Gayle guides it to midwicket
spins in from outside off, cut through backward point
from round the stumps arrives a back-of-length delivery on the off stump line, punched back down the track
Gayle chops it on. Length-delivery, homing in on the off stump, Gayle backs away a touch and tries to cut but he is cramped for room. He gets a inside-edge and the ball crashes into the stumps.
on the off and middle stump line, dabbed to the on side
fuller, slower in the air, outside off stump and Bravo lunges at it, takes the bottom-hand out, pushes it to cover.
full again, just outside off stump, Bravo pushes at it, edges it to backward point. One slip in place for him.
from round the stumps for Lara, in the zone outside off stump and it straightens. Lara lets it go through to the 'keeper
floated on the middle and leg stump line, Bravo waits, glances it fine. Delectable shot.
arm-ball, outside off stump, left alone.
lands on the off stump, turns away, Bravo dabs it to the on side.
flatter and outside off stump, cut to point and they set off for a risky run. Oram has a shy at the non-striker's end. If it was a direct hit, Bravo might have been found short of his crease.
leans forward, waits for the spin, turns it to the on side for a single. Easy.
floats in on the off stump line, turns away a touch, Bravo nudges it to the off side.
length-delivery, just outside off stump, Lara moves across, opens the blade, runs it down to third man
goes over the wickets for Bravo. Lands on a length, homes in on the off stump, pushed to the off side.
pitches on a length, outside off stump, bounces a bit, Bravo waits, places it towards cover point and will get a single.
comes in from outside off stump, Lara moves forward, drives on the up, to mid-off.
offers a bit of width outside off stump and Lara slashes at it, gets it down to widish third man. He wanted a second run but Vettori had moved in quickly.
slow through the air, on the off stump line, Lara leans forward, places it towards midwicket. He played it with soft hands and got an easy single as a reward.
lands outside off, slides on, Bravo leans back, taps it close on the off side, towards backward point and will get a run
faster, on the off stump line, some how Lara makes room to force it off the back foot, through cover
tossed up, on the off stump line, Bravo leans forward to dead-bat it
faster, on the off stump line, again they take a quick single with a dab to right of backward point.

almost run out. The prince would have been a pauper. Pushed towards close on the off side and he sets off,McCullum takes the gloves off,  picks the ball and takes aim at the non-striker's end. Lara is in the way, puts his bat out as shield, not to obstruct, the ball evades him but also misses the sticks and Lara survives.

More drama. Lara pulls a back of length delivery down the track. Bravo had skipped a few steps down the pitch, Oram stretches his left hand out, stops and hurls a throw at the non-striker's end. Bravo flings himself into the crease and the throw hits his left pad.
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
glances a length-delivery to backward short leg
Lara walks across, leans forward, whips a fullish delivery on the off stump line, to backward square-leg. Ala Saeed Anwar.
on the hips, clipped away to fine leg for a single
lands outside off, slides in, Bravo goes back and jabs it away
slightly short in length, outside off stump and Lara backs away to cut past point
outside off stump, again a touch short, and cut away to deep point
faster, fuller, on the middle stump, worked to midwicket
slower - Vettori continues to mix it around, outside off and Lara backs away to cut through backward point
slow through the air, around the off stump line, Bravo leans forward to defend
outside off stump, slanting away, Lara runs it down to third man
short in length, on the middle stump line, flicked away through square-leg
fuller, outside off stump, lashed away straight to backward point
slower, outside off stump, Lara reaches it, dabs it to third man
off cutter, on the off and middle, nudged to backward square-leg
faster, outside off stump and it shapes away a touch, Bravo has a nibble, misses and is beaten
full and on the off stump line, Lara threatens to charge down, arrests his front foot movement, drives to long on
slow through the air, on the middle stump line, paddled away for a single
quickish, on the off stump line, Lara has a forward press, then rocks back, late-cuts to short third man where Mason hurls in a throw, misses. Had he hit, Bravo might have been a goner.
on the middle and leg, swept for a single
tossed-up, outside off stump, Lara unfurls his special whiplash square-drive, out to sweeper cover
drifts in to the legs, Bravo flicks it through midwicket and will get two runs.
slow through the air, scrambled seam, on the off stump line, pushed through mid-off.
full in length, on the off stump line, tapped down the track
slips down to the pads, Bravo tries to force it away, doesn't make contact and the ball rolls off the pad
on the middle stump line, slightly short, Bravo goes back, whips it to midwicket where Marshall fumbles
back-of-length delivery, outside off stump and Lara cuts through backward point, Vettori rushes from third man to make a diving stop.
fullish, outside off stump and Lara drives inside-out through cover
slipping down the leg side, Lara shapes to sweep, misses and Vettori goes up in appeal. T'was going down leg.
flatter and on the middle stump line, driven to long on
The first four from Lara. arm-ball outside off stump and Lara leans back, late-cuts it past a diving short-third man fielder.

beaten in the flight. Lara was itching to come down the track, Vettori slows up the pace, makes it hang in the air and pushes it outside off stump. Lara stops his forward movement, slashes at it, gets a edge to short third man. Lovely cricket from Vettori.
slow through the air, outside off stump, Lara moves across, cuts through point
fuller, on the middle and off stump, Lara turns it to midwicket
shout for lbw. Length-delivery that landed outside off stump, moved in and Bravo is hit on the thigh pad while trying to work across the line. It was going over the sticks.
short of length, on the off stump line, cut to point
sliced over point. Dangerous. Fullish, outside off and Lara lashes at it, ends up slicing it over point and Oram can't get to it.
full in length, around off stump, driven to cover
slow through the air, on the middle and leg stump line, dabbed to the on side
Takes out Bravo straightaway. Drifts in the air, around off stump line and straightens, Bravo pushes at it, playing for the one that comes in and edges it to McCullum.
short in length, outside off stump, punched through cover point
fuller, on the off stump line, Ramdin stabs at it, gets a outside edge to point
What a response. Banged in short, on the middle stump line and Ramdin swivelled and pulled it  just behind square-leg.
Bond comes back with a slower one that teases the outside edge. Lands on a line outside off stump, straightens and Ramdin is beaten, pushing inside the line
another slower one, this time fullish, on the middle, driven back down the track
full, drifting on to the legs, tickled around the corner
edged between the legs of McCullum. Length-delivery, slanting away from Lara who goes for a cut, gets the bottom edge and it runs through the legs of McCullum who is standing up to the stumps.
fuller, angling away from the off stump, Lara opens the bat-face, runs it to third man
fullish, on the off and middle and suddenly Ramdin decides it has to go. Opts for a lofted-drive but goes too hard at it, gets a inside-edge on to the pad
short in length, on the middle stump , shoveled away to midwicket
lands on a length, around off, slides away, Lara wants to cut it late, gets a inside-edge on to the pad
Cute. Similar delivery, Lara goes back and across, opens the bat-face, and runs it down fine through the slip region. Oram dives, fumbles but recovers to pull the ball back in.
short in length, outside off, cut past point
around off stump line, Ramdin shuffles across, guides it through backward point
banged in short, on the off stump line - this is the second time that Bond has bounced at Ramdin- and Ramdin pulls it through midwicket.
slightly short in length, outside off stump, sliding away, Lara slashes it to third man
slow through the air, full in length, outside off, Ramdin edges it to third man

Lara walks. Fullish,  a off cutter, outside off stump and Lara opts for a ugly slog across the line, and gets a inside-edge to McCullum who is standing up to the stumps. Lara goes, trying to up the ante and West Indies slip further.
leans forward, pushes to point.
fuller, on the middle stump line, jabbed away to the off side
short of length, rises up outside off stump, cut down to point
turned to square leg
pushed down the ground to the bowler. Full length ball and Simmons keeps it away

patted to the on side, no run again. New Zealand have piled on the pressure right through and looking to mop it up now. West Indies have picked an extra batsman for this game. Let's see if that decision is going to work out
Tapped to the on side again
Worked away in front of square. Thinks of a second but they decide against it
Good length ball straight on middle, Simmons on the front foot and drives down the ground. Simmons has batted in the top order and would have the technique to counter the seamers
Tucked away to the on side. No run. Styris keeping it tight
Steered to third man, can't get runs again. Slowly but surely, pressure piling on
Tapped to the off side, another dot, another Pascal of pressure added to West Indies' barometer
Defended on the front foot back to the bowler. Seems to hit the pads first and a big appeal goes up. But he was way forward anyway. Tough to give those
Driven to cover but straight to the fielder. Maiden over from Styris
Full ball on leg, Ramdin tries to work it away but can't make contact

Flight and loop, pitched on middle and leg and spun away, Ramdin goes to play across the line and misses. Huge appeal for lbw and that was extremely close. Asad Rauf declines. Replays show that it was going on to hit middle. Good drift from Vettori there
Patted away to the off side.
Good loop again, pitching outside off, Ramdin tries to cut but it's too close to his body. He manages a mistime to short third man
Full and straight, driven back to the bowler. Second maiden on the trot. New Zealand closing in here.

Full ball on middle, Ramdin loves to sweep and goes for it again. He's struck on the pads and it trickles away to fine leg. Big appeal but not given again. Umpire calls a leg bye and that might have been very close as well. Replays show that some bat was involved
Square driven for a single. Batsmen trying ti inject some urgency with their running
Glided to third man for a single
Full ball just outside off, Simmons thinks of the drive but ends up digging out a near yorker. Drip, drip, drip
Drifting down leg and tucked away to the leg side for a single
Gives himself room and taps to the off side, straight to the fielder. It appears there are 20 NZ fielders out there. Everything going straight to the black shirts
on the off stump line, driven to the bowler
comes down the track, Vettori drags back the length, and he jabs it away to the off side

backs away, Vettori slows up the pace, tosses it up, it bounces up a touch and Ramdin goes for a cut, ends up tapping a dolly to point. To say that  West Indies are in deep trouble would be a understatement
again slow through the air, flighted, drifts in, Smith tries to go across the line , is rapped on the pads but the ball was spinning outside off. Vettori's appeal is turned down
There he goes. He knows to play only one way. Tossed-up on the middle and he swings it over deep midwicket
just outside off stump, slides on, cut to backward point
length-delivery on the middle, worked to right of Marshall at midwicket
fuller, on the off stump line, Simmons backs away a touch and unfurls a lovely square-drive
outside off stump, full in length, tapped to the off side
Two fours in Styris' last over. Simmons leans forward, swings a length-delivery on the middle, to long leg
lands on the middle stump, climbs up, Simmons walks across, tries to lap it around the corner, misses and it hits McCullum in his groin. Ouch.
full and outside off stump, Smith stays back and drives to long on
short in length, on the middle stump line, pulled to deep midwicket

Smith is cleaned up. Vettori floated it in the air, slow through the air, on the middle stump line and Smith shaped to sweep it across the line. He was too early into his stroke as the ball never arrived and slowly went on to peg the middle stump back

Two in two. Drifts in from round the stumps, on the middle stump line, Powell has a lazy waft, outside the line, and he is struck in front of middle and leg. It would have taken out leg stump. He is on a hat-trick.
full, on the middle stump line, pushed down the track
on the off stump line, dabbed away to the off side.
full, straight, on the off stump line, driven to long off
kicks up from short of length and thuds into the thigh pad
full and outside off stump and that teases the outside edge.
Screaming yorker, on the middle stump line, Collymore gets his bat down in a hurry, jabs at it but the ball rushes past the defensive blade and crashes into the middle stump.

inn2.comm: lands on a length, just outside off stump, straightens, Fulton moves in line, steers to point. Two slips in place.

What a start from Powell. A gem of a delivery to remove Fulton. Pitched on the good length, on the middle stump line, seamed away, evading the waft, and knocked out the middle stump. West Indies strike early.
short of length, on the off stump line, steered to third man

huge shout for a lbw. Full in length,on the off stump line, straightened a touch, Fleming leans across, doesn't offer a stroke and it brushes the back pad, enroute to Ramdin. But the ball didn't do enough, was not going to hit off stump. But Powell is on a mission here.
climbs up from short of length, outside off stump and Fleming shoulders arms
Full in the zone outside off stump, left alone
length-delivery, pushed to the off side

another scream for a lbw. It was pretty close. Landed on a length, outside off stump, bent in and struck him in front of off stump line. It would have taken out middle and leg. Umpire Rudi Koertzen doesn't concur. May be he felt the point of impact was outside off stump.
on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
climbs up from short of length, outside off stump, left alone
lands well outside off and veers further away
on the middle and leg stump line, glanced away behind square-leg
full in length, on the middle and leg, goes on straight, worked through square-leg
lands just short of Smith at third slip. Kicks up from short of length, moves away, Marshall pushes at it, gets a outside edge and luckily for him it falls short.
hits the deck short of length, on the middle stump line, Marshall gets behind the line and defends
drifting on to the legs, fullish and Marshall plays a nice pick-up shot, over square-leg
full, on the middle and off stump line, straightens, Marshall guides it, partly edged, partly steered, to third man
short of length, on the off stump line, Fleming jabs at it, gets a inside-edge on to the pad
Full and on the off stump line, driven to mid-off
rushes through the channel outside off stump, Marshall covers the off stump and shoulders arms
slightly short in length, outside the off stump, slashed away to third man
full in length, on the middle stump line, Fleming leans forward to work it to the on side
full in length, on the middle stump line, turned to the on side
slightly outside off stump, driven to cover
lands short of length, on middle and leg, moves in towards middle, Fleming leans forward, pushes it down the track. Two slips in place.
again kicks up short of length, around off stump, Fleming opens the bat-face, guides it to point
rushes through the channel outside off, slanting away, Fleming lets that one go through to Ramdin
fuller, around the off stump, driven to cover
length-delivery, outside off stump, pushed to point
classy. Fullish, on the off stump line and Fleming glides forward and caresses it straight down the ground.
lands on the off stump line, moves in, Marshall jabs at it, gets a outside edge, to the off side
lands on a length, outside off stump and Marshall tries to free his arms at the width but it's not the right length to cut and he mistimes the stroke towards point
fuller, just outside off stump, driven to mid-off

Simmons misses a run out chance. Marshall drove towards him and set off for a risky run. Simmons rushed in, picked and had a shy but misses and Marshall survives. Fleming calls Marshall over for a chat.
full and on the middle stump line, Fleming moves his front leg across and quickly takes it out of the line and drives to the on side.
on the middle and leg, full, Fleming flicks it through square-leg
slightly short in length, Fleming leans forward, shapes to pull, mistimes and it flies over the bowler's head. That could have been risky
lands on a length, on the middle and leg, Fleming shapes to pull but changes mind. Wise decision. Jabs it away to the on side
lands outside leg stump, moves in, Fleming leans forward and defends
Overpitched outside off stump and Fleming creams it through point. Lovely square-drive.
slants it away from Fleming who lets it go through to Ramdin
